```python
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# Define target materials
target_materials = ['plastic', 'aluminium', 'polypropylene', 'polystyrene', 'gold']

# Generate target material and thickness
np.random.seed(0)
target_thicknesses = np.random.lognormal(mean=1.02, sigma=np.sqrt(16.9), size=25)
target_materials_generated = np.random.choice(target_materials, size=25)

# Generate pulse width
pulse_widths = np.random.lognormal(mean=291, sigma=np.sqrt(1030000), size=25)

# Generate energy
energies = np.random.lognormal(mean=13.9, sigma=np.sqrt(2350), size=25)

# Generate spot size
spot_sizes = np.random.normal(mean=3.61, sigma=np.sqrt(13.7), size=25)

# Generate intensity
intensities = np.random.lognormal(mean=np.log(5.10e20), sigma=np.sqrt(np.log(3.96e41)), size=25)

# Generate power
powers = np.random.lognormal(mean=np.log(6.23e13), sigma=np.sqrt(np.log(4.03e27)), size=25)

# Generate cutoff energy
cutoff_energies = np.random.normal(mean=8.64, sigma=np.sqrt(156), size=25)

# Create data array
data = np.array(list(zip(target_materials_generated, target_thicknesses, pulse_widths, energies, spot_sizes, intensities, powers, cutoff_energies)))

print(data)
```
